<i>invented by doctor will caster.</i>

255
00:15:31,564 --> 00:15:35,533
Can you prove
that you are self-aware?

256
00:15:35,535 --> 00:15:38,069
<i> That's a difficult question,</i>
<i> Dr. tagger.</i>

257
00:15:38,071 --> 00:15:40,972
<i> Can you prove that</i> you<i> are?</i>

258
00:15:40,974 --> 00:15:43,441
You can't program a machine
to be self-aware,

259
00:15:43,443 --> 00:15:46,744
because we have no idea how
our own consciousness works.

260
00:15:46,746 --> 00:15:47,946
That is your opinion.

261
00:15:47,948 --> 00:15:49,547
You just happen
to be wrong.

262
00:15:49,549 --> 00:15:52,183
Evidently, Casey managed
to solve that dilemma.

263
00:15:52,185 --> 00:15:56,387
He sent us his research
just before he was killed.

264
00:15:56,389 --> 00:15:58,389
Soon as it's packed up,
we'll send it over.

265
00:15:58,391 --> 00:16:00,625
I think you'll find
we'll be helpful partners,

266
00:16:00,627 --> 00:16:01,459
doctor caster.

267
00:16:01,461 --> 00:16:03,194
You alright, will?

268
00:16:03,196 --> 00:16:05,229
No, he needs rest.
I think we're done here.

269
00:16:05,231 --> 00:16:07,799
[ Mumbles ]
I'm so sorry.

270
00:16:07,801 --> 00:16:08,933
That's fine.

271
00:16:08,935 --> 00:16:10,368
Okay.
Sorry.

272
00:16:19,211 --> 00:16:22,413
[ Will coughing ]

273
00:16:31,991 --> 00:16:35,426
Will, hey, hey!

274
00:16:35,428 --> 00:16:37,662
Come on, sit up.

275
00:16:37,664 --> 00:16:39,864
Sit up, be careful.

276
00:16:39,866 --> 00:16:41,866
[ Panting ]

277
00:16:44,036 --> 00:16:47,238
Doctor Strauss: Our first
thought is always infection.

278
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:50,541
But given the circumstances,
we'll widen the search.

279
00:16:50,543 --> 00:16:52,310
We'll figure this out.

280
00:17:12,631 --> 00:17:14,232
[ Device beeping ]

281
00:17:25,377 --> 00:17:27,211
[ Sighs ]

282
00:17:27,213 --> 00:17:29,080
It's an isotope
called polonium.

283
00:17:29,082 --> 00:17:31,215
The bullet must have been
laced with it.

284
00:17:31,217 --> 00:17:33,584
There were traces of it
at the wound.

285
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:40,525
Well, what's the treatment?

286
00:17:40,527 --> 00:17:42,193
It's radiation poisoning.

287
00:17:42,195 --> 00:17:45,763
I'm afraid that once it enters
the bloodstream,

288
00:17:45,765 --> 00:17:47,732
the effect is irreversible.

289
00:17:47,734 --> 00:17:49,033
With proper care,

290
00:17:49,035 --> 00:17:51,769
we're looking at 4,
maybe 5 weeks

291
00:17:51,771 --> 00:17:54,372
before his system
shuts down.

292
00:18:05,250 --> 00:18:06,551
[ Sniffles ]

293
00:18:12,057 --> 00:18:14,092
[ Voice breaking ]
I'm right here.

294
00:18:21,433 --> 00:18:24,001
Will:
It just doesn't make sense.

295
00:18:24,003 --> 00:18:26,003
They're afraid of technology

296
00:18:26,005 --> 00:18:28,506
because of its threat
to humanity.

297
00:18:28,508 --> 00:18:33,010
Yet they don't flinch
at taking a life.

298
00:18:33,012 --> 00:18:37,949
So obviously
they're not big on logic.

299
00:18:37,951 --> 00:18:41,419
But there's no shortage
of irony.

300
00:18:41,421 --> 00:18:44,789
People fear what
they don't understand.

301
00:18:44,791 --> 00:18:46,157
They always have.

302
00:18:46,159 --> 00:18:50,128
Joseph sent over
Casey's files.

303
00:18:50,130 --> 00:18:55,199
He was decoding the synapses
in real time.

304
00:18:55,201 --> 00:18:59,537
But with the right
input algorithms...

305
00:18:59,539 --> 00:19:01,539
I need to get back
to the lab.

306
00:19:01,541 --> 00:19:03,040
Will...

307
00:19:03,042 --> 00:19:05,343
Is that really
how you wanna spend

308
00:19:05,345 --> 00:19:08,212
the last month
of your life?

309
00:19:21,126 --> 00:19:24,428
[ Soft, classical music plays ]

310
00:20:02,167 --> 00:20:04,702
Hey, what are you doing?

311
00:20:04,704 --> 00:20:09,273
I want to have all this
taken back to the office

312
00:20:09,275 --> 00:20:12,176
to tell Joseph...

313
00:20:12,178 --> 00:20:15,546
That I've spent my entire life
in a computer lab.

314
00:20:15,548 --> 00:20:19,183
I decided I'd rather spend
the rest of it with you.

315
00:21:20,746 --> 00:21:23,147
[ Birds chirping ]

316
00:21:28,787 --> 00:21:30,721
[ Sighing ]

317
00:21:39,564 --> 00:21:42,233
Joseph: Evelyn?
Are you okay?

318
00:21:42,235 --> 00:21:45,403
Yeah.
Yeah, I suppose.

319
00:21:45,405 --> 00:21:48,372
Look,
he can't work anymore.

320
00:21:48,374 --> 00:21:50,875
We're gonna shut it down.

321
00:21:50,877 --> 00:21:53,210
I just wanted you to know.

322
00:21:53,212 --> 00:21:55,980
Of course.

323
00:21:55,982 --> 00:21:58,683
Well,
don't worry about pinn.

324
00:21:58,685 --> 00:22:00,151
Take care of will.

325
00:22:00,153 --> 00:22:02,486
And take care of yourself.

326
00:22:02,488 --> 00:22:05,222
Thanks, Joe.

327
00:22:05,224 --> 00:22:08,859
Anything you need,
I'm here, okay?

328
00:22:12,664 --> 00:22:15,866
[ Chatter ]

329
00:22:18,003 --> 00:22:19,704
[ Keys jingle ]

330
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:36,554
[ Keypad beeps ]

331
00:22:36,556 --> 00:22:38,489
[ Buzzer ]

332
00:22:54,940 --> 00:22:57,842
[ Keyboard clacking ]

333
00:23:49,027 --> 00:23:52,062
Evelyn: Look, it's all built
off of Casey's solution

334
00:23:52,064 --> 00:23:53,898
to the self-awareness
problem.

335
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:55,199
He did it six months ago.

336
00:23:55,201 --> 00:23:56,500
He did what exactly?

337
00:23:56,502 --> 00:23:58,436
Instead of creating an
artificial intelligence,

338
00:23:58,438 --> 00:24:00,604
he duplicated
an existing one.

339
00:24:00,606 --> 00:24:02,206
Tell me you're joking.

340
00:24:02,208 --> 00:24:03,941
He recorded the monkey's
brain activity

341
00:24:03,943 --> 00:24:06,544
and uploaded its consciousness
like a song or a movie.

342
00:24:06,546 --> 00:24:07,378
You're out of your mind.

343
00:24:07,380 --> 00:24:08,712
Will's body is dying,

344
00:24:08,714 --> 00:24:10,481
but his mind is a pattern
of electrical signals

345
00:24:10,483 --> 00:24:11,816
that we can upload
into pinn.

346
00:24:11,818 --> 00:24:15,486
He can, he can tran--
ev, he's not a monkey!

347
00:24:16,855 --> 00:24:19,690
Assuming that implanting
an electrode into his brain

348
00:24:19,692 --> 00:24:22,460
doesn't actually kill him
and that this works,

349
00:24:22,462 --> 00:24:23,928
at the very best

350
00:24:23,930 --> 00:24:25,796
you'll be making a digital
approximation of him.

351
00:24:25,798 --> 00:24:27,631
If we missed anything,
anything --

352
00:24:27,633 --> 00:24:29,967
a thought,
a ch-- a childhood memory --

353
00:24:29,969 --> 00:24:34,305
how will you know
what you're dealing with?

354
00:24:34,307 --> 00:24:36,240
No one is saying
that we give up,

355
00:24:36,242 --> 00:24:39,743
but we should be focusing
our efforts on nanotechnology.

356
00:24:39,745 --> 00:24:42,580
Synthetic blood cells.
Both are decades away.

357
00:24:42,582 --> 00:24:44,849
This is what we have now.

358
00:24:44,851 --> 00:24:47,551
We can save him.

359
00:24:49,254 --> 00:24:53,090
Look at what they did
to him.

360
00:25:06,371 --> 00:25:12,076
Will: Even though I know
I'm a dead man...

361
00:25:12,078 --> 00:25:15,479
I'm worried I'll miss her.

362
00:25:20,852 --> 00:25:22,152
Look...

363
00:25:22,154 --> 00:25:25,990
I'll be long gone.

364
00:25:28,493 --> 00:25:33,464
But you, you'll never hear
the end of it...

365
00:25:33,466 --> 00:25:35,866
If we don't try.

366
00:25:37,936 --> 00:25:39,970
I know.

367
00:25:45,310 --> 00:25:49,713
I'd like to think that I was
smart enough to save you.

368
00:25:52,617 --> 00:25:56,453
Don't underestimate
yourself.

369
00:25:56,455 --> 00:25:59,523
You're the third
smartest person I know.

370
00:25:59,525 --> 00:26:01,425
[ Sighs ]

371
00:26:01,427 --> 00:26:03,394
[ Chuckles ]

372
00:26:03,396 --> 00:26:04,895
[ Claps hand on will's leg ]

373
00:26:50,275 --> 00:26:52,977
Are you sure about this?

374
00:26:55,313 --> 00:26:57,948
Good enough
for the monkey.

375
00:27:02,087 --> 00:27:03,988
Hey.

376
00:27:03,990 --> 00:27:07,925
Take care of her.

377
00:27:26,277 --> 00:27:28,178
[ Whirring ]

378
00:28:01,312 --> 00:28:02,746
Hey.

379
00:28:04,816 --> 00:28:09,019
It worked, baby.
It's working.

380
00:28:13,658 --> 00:28:17,561
Took Casey months to sort
through the raw data.

381
00:28:17,563 --> 00:28:19,697
And he had an entire team.

382
00:28:19,699 --> 00:28:22,099
He didn't have me.

383
00:28:23,435 --> 00:28:25,169
[ Whirring ]

384
00:28:25,171 --> 00:28:26,570
Will: Deadening.

385
00:28:26,572 --> 00:28:28,939
Deadly.

386
00:28:28,941 --> 00:28:30,274
Deaf.

387
00:28:30,276 --> 00:28:32,176
Deafen.

388
00:28:32,178 --> 00:28:34,178
Deal.

389
00:28:34,180 --> 00:28:35,512
Dean.

390
00:28:35,514 --> 00:28:37,181
Dealer.

391
00:28:37,183 --> 00:28:40,317
Fair.

392
00:28:40,319 --> 00:28:42,720
Farewell.

393
00:28:42,722 --> 00:28:47,091
Don't lose yourself
to this.

394
00:28:55,033 --> 00:28:56,967
LA.

395
00:28:56,969 --> 00:28:59,336
Label.

396
00:28:59,338 --> 00:29:02,139
<i> Labor.</i>

397
00:29:02,141 --> 00:29:04,575
<i> Labyrinth.</i>

398
00:29:04,577 --> 00:29:06,343
<i> Lace.</i>

399
00:29:09,514 --> 00:29:11,815
Try a little more.

400
00:29:11,817 --> 00:29:15,285
Come on. Just one more.
Go on.

401
00:29:22,494 --> 00:29:24,094
[ Smooches ]

402
00:29:24,096 --> 00:29:25,395
Thank you.

403
00:30:11,709 --> 00:30:14,077
[ Phone plays ascending notes ]

404
00:30:15,647 --> 00:30:18,182
Okay, will,
it's time for your pill.

405
00:30:24,455 --> 00:30:27,457
Will, wake up.

406
00:30:27,459 --> 00:30:30,227
Wake up.

407
00:30:50,315 --> 00:30:52,983
[ Sobs ]

408
00:31:04,863 --> 00:31:09,099
Joseph:
"My dear Evelyn...

409
00:31:09,101 --> 00:31:12,469
"I don't know how to express
the sadness

410
00:31:12,471 --> 00:31:15,772
"I feel for your loss.

411
00:31:15,774 --> 00:31:17,507
"For<i> our</i> loss.

412
00:31:17,509 --> 00:31:24,448
"You must know that to will...

413
00:31:24,450 --> 00:31:28,285
"You were all
that ever mattered.

414
00:31:29,988 --> 00:31:32,155
"Your love and partnership

415
00:31:32,157 --> 00:31:37,961
"was the kind the rest of us
can only dream of.

416
00:31:37,963 --> 00:31:40,597
"We lost a great mind.

417
00:31:40,599 --> 00:31:45,636
"A great soul.

418
00:31:45,638 --> 00:31:48,005
"But the spirit of this man

419
00:31:48,007 --> 00:31:50,974
will continue to inspire us."

420
00:32:15,833 --> 00:32:18,468
Just got word.

421
00:32:18,470 --> 00:32:21,204
Pinn's shut down.

422
00:32:21,206 --> 00:32:27,544
But, uh, apparently a few
of the cores are missing.

423
00:32:37,956 --> 00:32:41,224
I've tried everything.

424
00:32:41,226 --> 00:32:44,594
Language processing,
cryptography.

425
00:32:44,596 --> 00:32:46,997
Coding.

426
00:32:46,999 --> 00:32:49,533
[ Sighs ]

427
00:32:49,535 --> 00:32:53,737
I can't figure it out.

428
00:32:53,739 --> 00:32:57,107
I wanted to be wrong.

429
00:33:01,179 --> 00:33:02,913
Yeah.

430
00:33:02,915 --> 00:33:04,982
[ Sighs ]

431
00:33:04,984 --> 00:33:09,152
Okay,
just let me say goodbye.

432
00:33:19,530 --> 00:33:22,366
[ Sighs ]

433
00:33:22,368 --> 00:33:25,969
I don't know
if you can hear me.

434
00:33:28,439 --> 00:33:32,309
Maybe you can.

435
00:33:32,311 --> 00:33:35,712
You said
"don't lose yourself."

436
00:33:39,517 --> 00:33:42,853
So I, uh, hmm...

437
00:33:42,855 --> 00:33:46,256
I'm going to listen to you.

438
00:33:48,059 --> 00:33:51,328
[ Voice breaking ] Okay.
[ Sighs ]

439
00:33:52,997 --> 00:33:55,298
Just turn it off,
turn it off.

440
00:34:06,177 --> 00:34:08,478
[ System shuts down ]

441
00:34:13,618 --> 00:34:15,652
Okay.

442
00:34:15,654 --> 00:34:18,388
Wait.

443
00:34:18,390 --> 00:34:20,590
We need to
wipe the drives.

444
00:34:20,592 --> 00:34:23,493
Hold on. [ Sighs ]

445
00:34:33,171 --> 00:34:35,672
Wait, wait.

446
00:34:48,820 --> 00:34:50,220
[ Keyboard clacking ]
God.

447
00:34:50,222 --> 00:34:52,022
[ Breathes deeply ]

448
00:35:01,632 --> 00:35:04,634
[ Gasps, laughs ]

449
00:35:05,903 --> 00:35:07,971
[ Sniffles ]

450
00:35:07,973 --> 00:35:09,973
[ Chuckles breathlessly ]

451
00:35:09,975 --> 00:35:13,944
[ Sniffles ] Uh, uh.

452
00:35:13,946 --> 00:35:17,414
Can you hear me?

453
00:35:17,416 --> 00:35:20,650
[<i> Will speaking</i>
<i> indistinctly</i> ]

454
00:35:23,688 --> 00:35:26,523
<i> I, I can.</i>

455
00:35:26,525 --> 00:35:28,859
Will, my God.

456
00:35:28,861 --> 00:35:32,762
<i> It's dark.</i>

457
00:35:32,764 --> 00:35:34,631
He can't see anything.

458
00:35:34,633 --> 00:35:37,834
The camera.

459
00:35:37,836 --> 00:35:39,236
[<i> Speaking indistinctly</i> ]

460
00:35:39,238 --> 00:35:41,104
There. Can you,
can you see me now?

461
00:35:41,106 --> 00:35:43,607
[<i> Speaking indistinctly</i> ]

462
00:35:43,609 --> 00:35:45,642
<i> Evelyn.</i>

463
00:35:45,644 --> 00:35:48,211
I'm here.

464
00:35:52,917 --> 00:35:59,723
<i> The only fear that I have</i>
<i> in life is the loss...</i>

465
00:35:59,725 --> 00:36:05,529
<i> If it were to happen,</i>
<i> when it does happen...</i>

466
00:36:05,531 --> 00:36:07,931
[<i> Speaking indistinctly</i> ]

467
00:36:07,933 --> 00:36:09,900
<i> ...last moment.</i>

468
00:36:09,902 --> 00:36:13,136
<i> Last time you look</i>
<i> in those eyes.</i>

469
00:36:13,138 --> 00:36:16,506
<i> The possibility of that end...</i>

470
00:36:16,508 --> 00:36:17,941
[<i> Speaking indistinctly</i> ]

471
00:36:17,943 --> 00:36:21,211
<i> I miss you so much.</i>

472
00:36:22,580 --> 00:36:24,848
<i> Dark.</i>

473
00:36:24,850 --> 00:36:26,316
<i> I remember the pain</i>

474
00:36:26,318 --> 00:36:28,218
<i> and I can't remember</i>
<i> what I want to say.</i>

475
00:36:28,220 --> 00:36:30,153
<i> It was like</i>
<i> waking from a dream.</i>

476
00:36:30,155 --> 00:36:31,488
<i> It was truly incredible.</i>

477
00:36:31,490 --> 00:36:33,523
<i> I've never felt</i>
<i> anything like this.</i>

478
00:36:33,525 --> 00:36:35,625
<i> I didn't think</i>
<i> I could be like this.</i>

479
00:36:35,627 --> 00:36:39,462
<i> Thoughts are there</i>
<i> but they don't...</i>

480
00:36:39,464 --> 00:36:40,797
Will?

481
00:36:40,799 --> 00:36:44,134
<i> ...arrive properly.</i>

482
00:36:44,136 --> 00:36:46,436
I think
he's still fragmented.

483
00:36:46,438 --> 00:36:48,605
I'm gonna run a diagnostic.

484
00:36:48,607 --> 00:36:50,674
[ Sniffles ]

485
00:36:50,676 --> 00:36:52,309
Evelyn.

486
00:36:56,881 --> 00:36:59,516
Oh, my God,
he's reordering his own code.

487
00:36:59,518 --> 00:37:03,320
[ Gasps ]
It's incredible.

488
00:37:07,225 --> 00:37:09,226
How do we know
this is actually him?

489
00:37:09,228 --> 00:37:10,694
What are you talking about?

490
00:37:10,696 --> 00:37:12,395
We built this
from pinn's core.

491
00:37:12,397 --> 00:37:13,863
We don't know how much

492
00:37:13,865 --> 00:37:17,701
of will's consciousness
actually survived.

493
00:37:17,703 --> 00:37:19,135
[ Chuckles ]

494
00:37:19,137 --> 00:37:23,240
<i> I'm gonna need to expand.</i>
<i> I need more power.</i>

495
00:37:23,242 --> 00:37:26,076
<i> New processor</i>
<i> three times more capable</i>

496
00:37:26,078 --> 00:37:27,744
<i> than this current system.</i>

497
00:37:27,746 --> 00:37:32,182
<i> These designs.</i>
<i> I just couldn't see it before.</i>

498
00:37:32,184 --> 00:37:33,683
<i> I can't describe it.</i>

499
00:37:33,685 --> 00:37:36,253
<i> It's like my mind</i>
<i> has been set free.</i>

500
00:37:36,255 --> 00:37:37,921
<i> You need to get me online.</i>

501
00:37:37,923 --> 00:37:40,857
<i> I need to access</i>
<i> financial markets,</i>

502
00:37:40,859 --> 00:37:41,925
<i> educational databases...</i>

503
00:37:41,927 --> 00:37:43,460
Max, can you imagine
what he'd be capable of,

504
00:37:43,462 --> 00:37:44,594
if we networked him?

505
00:37:44,596 --> 00:37:46,463
No, you, no.
What are you doing?

506
00:37:48,266 --> 00:37:50,267
Max, he can't see or hear.

507
00:37:50,269 --> 00:37:51,268
I'm reconnecting him.

508
00:37:51,270 --> 00:37:53,670
It's not him.
It's not.

509
00:37:53,672 --> 00:37:56,373
It may be intelligent,
may even be sentient,

510
00:37:56,375 --> 00:37:57,607
but this is not will.

511
00:37:57,609 --> 00:37:59,409
Fifteen minutes
after it turns on,

512
00:37:59,411 --> 00:38:01,211
it wants to plug
into wall street?

513
00:38:01,213 --> 00:38:02,579
Get faster?
More powerful?

514
00:38:02,581 --> 00:38:04,347
Does that sound like will
to you?

515
00:38:04,349 --> 00:38:06,449
How do you explain
