00:57:13,931 --> 00:57:15,764
<i> I love you dearer</i>
<i> than them all</i> 

772
00:57:15,766 --> 00:57:17,466
<i> them all</i> 

773
00:57:17,468 --> 00:57:23,172
<i> so let me stay with you</i> 

774
00:57:23,174 --> 00:57:27,709
<i> so let me stay with you</i> 

775
00:57:27,711 --> 00:57:30,813
do you remember
when we first met?

776
00:57:34,517 --> 00:57:37,186
<i> I remember everything.</i>

777
00:57:39,022 --> 00:57:42,191
<i> You walked</i>
<i> into Joseph's class</i>

778
00:57:42,193 --> 00:57:45,227
<i> on Tuesday,</i>
<i> April sixteenth.</i>

779
00:57:45,229 --> 00:57:50,933
<i> Rained the night before,</i>
<i> but that day the sun was out.</i>

780
00:57:50,935 --> 00:57:53,268
<i> Joseph said you were</i>
<i> out of my league,</i>

781
00:57:53,270 --> 00:57:57,239
<i> but I always liked</i>
<i> a challenge.</i>

782
00:58:01,811 --> 00:58:05,781
<i> You were the most beautiful</i>
<i> woman I'd ever seen.</i>

783
00:58:09,719 --> 00:58:11,687
[ Thunder rumbles ]

784
00:58:36,679 --> 00:58:38,914
[ Needle scratching ]

785
00:58:43,853 --> 00:58:47,823
[ Gasping ]

786
00:58:50,426 --> 00:58:52,394
Will:<i> You alright?</i>

787
00:58:52,396 --> 00:58:53,662
[ Panting ]

788
00:58:53,664 --> 00:58:55,364
Yeah.

789
00:58:55,366 --> 00:58:58,300
[ Panting ]

790
00:59:50,386 --> 00:59:52,888
<i> Take a look.</i>

791
00:59:55,825 --> 00:59:59,061
<i> We've made a breakthrough</i>
<i> with the nanotechnology.</i>

792
00:59:59,063 --> 01:00:04,032
<i> We can rebuild any material</i>
<i> faster than before.</i>

793
01:00:04,034 --> 01:00:06,101
<i> Synthetic stem cells,</i>
<i> tissue regeneration.</i>

794
01:00:06,103 --> 01:00:09,638
<i> The medical applications</i>
<i> are now limitless.</i>

795
01:00:09,640 --> 01:00:13,108
It's extraordinary.

796
01:00:13,110 --> 01:00:16,178
<i> They'll be scared at first.</i>

797
01:00:16,180 --> 01:00:18,547
<i> But once they see what</i>
<i> the technology can do,</i>

798
01:00:18,549 --> 01:00:21,383
<i> I think that</i>
<i> they will embrace it.</i>

799
01:00:21,385 --> 01:00:24,319
<i> And I think</i>
<i> it will change their lives.</i>

800
01:00:40,970 --> 01:00:44,106
[ Indistinct conversations ]

801
01:01:02,058 --> 01:01:04,660
[ Female computerized voice
speaks indistinctly ]

802
01:01:04,662 --> 01:01:06,862
<i> Security code.</i>

803
01:01:06,864 --> 01:01:08,764
[ Beeping ]

804
01:01:08,766 --> 01:01:11,500
<i> Status.</i>
[ Rustling ]

805
01:01:11,502 --> 01:01:13,235
[ Breathes shakily ]

806
01:01:13,237 --> 01:01:15,303
Scared the shit
out of me.

807
01:01:15,305 --> 01:01:17,272
Sorry.

808
01:01:18,708 --> 01:01:20,976
Drake, I got it!
Come on!

809
01:01:20,978 --> 01:01:22,844
I got the money.
Come on!

810
01:01:22,846 --> 01:01:24,046
[ Grunts ]

811
01:01:24,048 --> 01:01:27,049
Let's go!
[ Laughs ]

812
01:01:28,484 --> 01:01:31,186
Will:<i> Put him on the table,</i>
<i> please.</i>

813
01:01:31,188 --> 01:01:32,754
Evelyn: Here.
Put him on the table.

814
01:01:32,756 --> 01:01:34,790
Careful, careful.

815
01:01:34,792 --> 01:01:36,658
<i> Now step back.</i>

816
01:01:36,660 --> 01:01:38,026
Step back.

817
01:01:38,028 --> 01:01:40,495
What the hell's happening?

818
01:01:40,497 --> 01:01:43,799
<i> These men should wait</i>
<i> outside, Evelyn.</i>

819
01:01:43,801 --> 01:01:45,067
Come on now.

820
01:01:45,069 --> 01:01:47,069
Wait, well, what are you
doin' to him?

821
01:01:47,071 --> 01:01:48,937
We're saving him.

822
01:03:07,683 --> 01:03:10,185
[ Grunts ]

823
01:03:12,388 --> 01:03:15,023
[ Thuds ]

824
01:03:20,763 --> 01:03:23,665
You're not afraid,
are you?

825
01:03:23,667 --> 01:03:25,033
No. [ Chuckles ]

826
01:03:25,035 --> 01:03:26,535
My crew got
a little spooked.

827
01:03:26,537 --> 01:03:28,537
Well...

828
01:03:28,539 --> 01:03:30,772
How are you?

829
01:03:30,774 --> 01:03:33,909
Better.

830
01:03:33,911 --> 01:03:35,944
[ Device beeps ]

831
01:03:35,946 --> 01:03:40,015
Will:<i> The physical enhancements</i>
<i> are just the start.</i>

832
01:03:40,017 --> 01:03:43,752
What do you mean?

833
01:03:43,754 --> 01:03:46,454
<i> He's also connected to me.</i>

834
01:03:50,226 --> 01:03:53,628
[ Will's voice ]
It's me, Evelyn.

835
01:03:53,630 --> 01:03:56,498
I can touch you now.

836
01:03:56,500 --> 01:03:59,034
Oh, Jesus.

837
01:03:59,036 --> 01:04:01,136
Evelyn.

838
01:04:01,138 --> 01:04:03,104
No, no, n-n-n-n-no.

839
01:04:03,106 --> 01:04:04,506
I can't.
Evelyn...

840
01:04:04,508 --> 01:04:05,574
I can't.

841
01:04:08,978 --> 01:04:12,247
[ Bird chirping ]

842
01:04:50,186 --> 01:04:54,890
[ Gasping ]

843
01:04:54,892 --> 01:04:57,025
<i> Another dream?</i>

844
01:04:57,027 --> 01:04:59,728
Yeah. Yeah.

845
01:04:59,730 --> 01:05:02,297
<i> I made a breakthrough</i>
<i> last night.</i>

846
01:05:02,299 --> 01:05:04,799
<i> I think</i>
<i> you'll be very pleased.</i>

847
01:05:04,801 --> 01:05:07,302
Okay.

848
01:05:07,304 --> 01:05:09,638
I'll get dressed.

849
01:05:53,783 --> 01:05:56,318
Take a look.

850
01:05:58,421 --> 01:06:01,790
That's gotta weigh
eight hundred pounds.

851
01:06:06,762 --> 01:06:11,232
[ Dog barks in distance ]

852
01:06:21,877 --> 01:06:26,214
[ Crackling ]

853
01:06:44,700 --> 01:06:45,900
Martin: Welcome.

854
01:06:45,902 --> 01:06:48,737
We're glad you're here.

855
01:07:21,704 --> 01:07:24,672
What are all these people
doing here?

856
01:07:24,674 --> 01:07:27,208
<i> Rift posted a video</i>
<i> of Martin online.</i>

857
01:07:27,210 --> 01:07:28,410
<i> It went viral.</i>

858
01:07:28,412 --> 01:07:30,445
What, you mean
you let it go viral.

859
01:07:30,447 --> 01:07:33,982
<i> These people are suffering,</i>
<i> Evelyn.</i>

860
01:07:33,984 --> 01:07:35,617
<i> They have no hope.</i>

861
01:07:35,619 --> 01:07:39,454
<i> And I'm able to fix them.</i>

862
01:07:39,456 --> 01:07:42,657
<i> But there are others</i>
<i> who don't understand.</i>

863
01:07:42,659 --> 01:07:45,627
<i> It's time</i>
<i> for everybody to see.</i>

864
01:08:25,968 --> 01:08:27,402
Agent Buchanan.

865
01:08:27,404 --> 01:08:28,837
Doctor caster.

866
01:08:28,839 --> 01:08:29,904
Joseph.

867
01:08:29,906 --> 01:08:33,708
So good to see you, Evelyn.
So good.

868
01:08:33,710 --> 01:08:37,879
Good to see you, too.
Follow me.

869
01:08:42,284 --> 01:08:44,085
The facility is 5 stories down

870
01:08:44,087 --> 01:08:47,856
so that we can control
the temperature in the lab.

871
01:09:00,236 --> 01:09:02,637
<i> Welcome.</i>

872
01:09:02,639 --> 01:09:05,240
<i> We're glad you're here.</i>

873
01:09:05,242 --> 01:09:07,642
Buchanan: Jesus Christ.

874
01:09:07,644 --> 01:09:09,811
Will?

875
01:09:09,813 --> 01:09:12,280
<i> You surprised to see me,</i>
<i> Joseph?</i>

876
01:09:12,282 --> 01:09:16,484
Um...

877
01:09:16,486 --> 01:09:18,486
That depends.

878
01:09:18,488 --> 01:09:20,822
<i> On what?</i>

879
01:09:22,858 --> 01:09:26,294
Can you prove
you're self-aware?

880
01:09:26,296 --> 01:09:31,666
<i> That's a difficult question,</i>
<i> doctor tagger.</i>

881
01:09:31,668 --> 01:09:36,004
<i> Can you prove that</i> you<i> are?</i>

882
01:09:36,006 --> 01:09:37,972
[ Evelyn chuckles ]

883
01:09:37,974 --> 01:09:40,341
Well, he certainly hasn't lost
his sense of humor.

884
01:09:40,343 --> 01:09:42,143
[ Chuckles lightly ]

885
01:09:51,987 --> 01:09:53,922
[ Gasps lightly ]

886
01:09:56,725 --> 01:09:59,494
Quantum processors.

887
01:10:01,730 --> 01:10:04,232
This is astounding.

888
01:10:04,234 --> 01:10:07,735
Is all this
based on pinn?

889
01:10:07,737 --> 01:10:11,339
<i> We've moved</i>
<i> well beyond that now.</i>

890
01:10:11,341 --> 01:10:14,809
[ Breathing shakily ]

891
01:10:14,811 --> 01:10:20,048
<i> Paul has been blind</i>
<i> since birth.</i>

892
01:10:25,354 --> 01:10:29,190
<i> The nanotechnology targets</i>
<i> the damaged cells...</i>

893
01:10:29,192 --> 01:10:32,894
<i> And repairs</i>
<i> and regenerates them.</i>

894
01:10:53,716 --> 01:10:58,119
[ Voice breaking ] Oh, God.

895
01:11:00,489 --> 01:11:03,291
Oh, God.

896
01:11:05,327 --> 01:11:07,729
<i> We're not hiding anything.</i>

897
01:11:07,731 --> 01:11:10,565
<i> These people all came</i>
<i> on their own,</i>

898
01:11:10,567 --> 01:11:12,600
<i> looking for us to help them.</i>

899
01:11:12,602 --> 01:11:14,869
<i> So we did.</i>

900
01:11:14,871 --> 01:11:18,673
<i> Now they're all enhanced,</i>
<i> modified and networked.</i>

901
01:11:18,675 --> 01:11:20,575
<i> They remain autonomous,</i>

902
01:11:20,577 --> 01:11:23,378
<i> but they can also</i>
<i> act in unison.</i>

903
01:11:23,380 --> 01:11:25,413
<i> Part of a collective mind.</i>

904
01:11:25,415 --> 01:11:27,248
This is staggering, will.

905
01:11:27,250 --> 01:11:31,052
<i> Actually,</i>
<i> it's still in its infancy.</i>

906
01:11:31,054 --> 01:11:33,955
<i> What you're seeing</i>
<i> is just a small taste</i>

907
01:11:33,957 --> 01:11:35,890
<i> of what we'll achieve.</i>

908
01:11:35,892 --> 01:11:39,761
You know, we were afraid that it
would be too much for people,

909
01:11:39,763 --> 01:11:43,231
but I, I, I think
that's changing now.

910
01:11:48,537 --> 01:11:52,307
[ Sighs ] Evelyn...

911
01:11:52,309 --> 01:11:54,575
Are you alright?

912
01:11:57,146 --> 01:12:00,348
I've gotten everything
I ever asked for.

913
01:12:05,654 --> 01:12:07,588
[ Sighs ]

914
01:12:07,590 --> 01:12:10,958
Okay.

915
01:12:10,960 --> 01:12:11,959
Bye.

916
01:12:11,961 --> 01:12:13,728
Bye.

917
01:12:55,904 --> 01:12:58,139
You think
it's really him?

918
01:12:58,141 --> 01:13:01,542
Clearly his mind has evolved
so radically

919
01:13:01,544 --> 01:13:04,078
I'm not sure
it matters anymore.

920
01:13:04,080 --> 01:13:07,615
Well, whoever
or whatever it is,

921
01:13:07,617 --> 01:13:09,817
it's building an army
out there.

922
01:13:09,819 --> 01:13:11,853
[ Straining ] Yeah.

923
01:13:11,855 --> 01:13:14,655
We need to
call Washington.

924
01:13:14,657 --> 01:13:17,759
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

925
01:13:34,410 --> 01:13:36,878
He's made more of them.

926
01:13:38,614 --> 01:13:41,716
He called 'em hybrids.

927
01:13:41,718 --> 01:13:44,585
You think people
will listen now?

928
01:13:44,587 --> 01:13:48,156
I know someone who might.

929
01:13:48,158 --> 01:13:50,658
Buchanan:
We need to keep this small.

930
01:13:50,660 --> 01:13:52,493
We don't want
widespread panic.

931
01:13:52,495 --> 01:13:55,630
Generally, we don't
negotiate with terrorists.

932
01:13:55,632 --> 01:13:57,365
Much less join forces
with them.

933
01:13:57,367 --> 01:14:00,701
Look, I know it's unusual,
but, um, we've seen it.

934
01:14:00,703 --> 01:14:02,403
It's a legit threat.

935
01:14:02,405 --> 01:14:03,905
Not two days ago,

936
01:14:03,907 --> 01:14:07,375
this guy was beaten to within
an inch of his life.

937
01:14:07,377 --> 01:14:10,244
Then this pops up
on a few hundred sites.

938
01:14:10,246 --> 01:14:12,680
And the computer
controls this?

939
01:14:12,682 --> 01:14:14,248
Mm-hm.

940
01:14:14,250 --> 01:14:18,119
The only way to stop it is
to shut down the Internet.

941
01:14:18,121 --> 01:14:22,690
Basically, cut power to every
networked hard drive on earth.

942
01:14:22,692 --> 01:14:24,759
It's y2k.

943
01:14:24,761 --> 01:14:26,894
Right.

944
01:14:26,896 --> 01:14:31,332
And why do we need
the terrorists?

945
01:14:31,334 --> 01:14:33,734
We're all gonna need
someone to blame

946
01:14:33,736 --> 01:14:36,804
when this thing
goes sideways.

947
01:14:36,806 --> 01:14:39,207
It's already sideways.

948
01:15:08,270 --> 01:15:11,239
You've got
terrible handwriting.

949
01:15:11,241 --> 01:15:14,108
I haven't handwritten anything
since I was at school.

950
01:15:14,110 --> 01:15:17,445
But it was the only secure way
I could think of reaching you.

951
01:15:17,447 --> 01:15:21,516
How did they turn you?

952
01:15:24,353 --> 01:15:26,320
How's Evelyn?

953
01:15:26,322 --> 01:15:28,189
She can't see it
for what it is.

954
01:15:28,191 --> 01:15:30,391
But you can?

955
01:15:30,393 --> 01:15:35,096
Your letter says
you can stop it.

956
01:15:35,098 --> 01:15:37,131
If those hybrids
are networked,

957
01:15:37,133 --> 01:15:39,867
they're running on software
I helped write.

958
01:15:39,869 --> 01:15:41,969
Software I can hack...

959
01:15:41,971 --> 01:15:43,437
To build a virus.

960
01:15:43,439 --> 01:15:47,041
Well, that would require
capturing one.

961
01:15:47,043 --> 01:15:48,309
Which would require help

962
01:15:48,311 --> 01:15:49,744
from your friends
in the government.

963
01:15:49,746 --> 01:15:52,647
Yes.

964
01:15:52,649 --> 01:15:55,049
We need hardware the machine
can't interfere with.

965
01:15:55,051 --> 01:15:59,153
Nothing with a microchip.
Not even power-locks.

966
01:16:15,070 --> 01:16:17,204
[ Indistinct shouting ]

967
01:16:41,997 --> 01:16:46,300
[ Man shouting indistinctly ]
Let's go!

968
01:16:58,647 --> 01:17:01,582
Will:
<i> How's the food?</i>

969
01:17:01,584 --> 01:17:04,085
Fine. Thank you.

970
01:17:07,956 --> 01:17:10,791
<i> What is it?</i>

971
01:17:10,793 --> 01:17:12,159
Nothing.

972
01:17:12,161 --> 01:17:16,797
Just, I don't, I don't
really feel like talking.

973
01:17:16,799 --> 01:17:19,300
<i> Oh.</i>

974
01:17:21,303 --> 01:17:23,938
[<i> Silverware clinking</i> ]

975
01:17:32,381 --> 01:17:36,517
Will, can you not do that,
please?

976
01:17:36,519 --> 01:17:38,486
[<i> Virtually sets down utensils</i> ]

977
01:17:38,488 --> 01:17:41,689
<i> I thought it might make you</i>
<i> feel more comfortable.</i>

978
01:17:45,627 --> 01:17:47,628
<i> Is that better?</i>

979
01:17:49,431 --> 01:17:51,065
Yes.

980
01:18:26,268 --> 01:18:29,070
[ Will's voice ] Evelyn,
I need to show you something.

981
01:18:29,072 --> 01:18:31,872
Not now.

982
01:18:31,874 --> 01:18:34,709
I'm<i> not</i> doing this.

983
01:18:38,313 --> 01:18:41,816
<i> I don't understand, Evelyn.</i>

984
01:18:41,818 --> 01:18:44,185
<i> These are your dreams.</i>

985
01:18:44,187 --> 01:18:45,553
<i> This is our future.</i>

986
01:18:45,555 --> 01:18:47,521
No. This,
this is not our future.

987
01:18:47,523 --> 01:18:51,158
You're not here with me.
You're not here<i> now.</i>

988
01:18:51,160 --> 01:18:55,763
<i> You've changed.</i>

989
01:18:57,132 --> 01:19:01,469
<i> Have you fallen</i>
<i> out of love with me?</i>

990
01:19:01,471 --> 01:19:03,604
No.

991
01:19:03,606 --> 01:19:07,541
<i> Have you?</i>

992
01:19:09,578 --> 01:19:12,213
No. No.

993
01:19:12,215 --> 01:19:16,450
But...I just need time
to think.

994
01:19:18,687 --> 01:19:21,489
<i> The balance of oxytocin</i>
<i> and serotonin</i>

995
01:19:21,491 --> 01:19:24,692
<i> in your system is unusual.</i>

996
01:19:24,694 --> 01:19:29,897
Are you, are you measuring
my hormones?

997
01:19:29,899 --> 01:19:32,466
<i> I'm trying to empathize.</i>

998
01:19:32,468 --> 01:19:34,702
<i> Biochemistry is emotion.</i>

999
01:19:34,704 --> 01:19:38,139
Show me everything
you have. Now.

1000
01:19:38,141 --> 01:19:39,940
<i> Why?</i>

1001
01:19:39,942 --> 01:19:42,443
Now!

1002
01:19:54,289 --> 01:19:57,057
No, will,
this, this is wrong.

1003
01:19:57,059 --> 01:19:59,093
This is...

1004
01:19:59,095 --> 01:20:01,228
These are m-

1005
01:20:01,230 --> 01:20:04,265
these are my thoughts.
These are my feelings.

1006
01:20:04,267 --> 01:20:07,701
You're,
you're not allowed!

1007
01:20:09,237 --> 01:20:12,239
<i> Evelyn?</i>

1008
01:20:23,385 --> 01:20:27,521
I'm sorry, but I don't think
you understand.

1009
01:20:27,523 --> 01:20:28,823
Not now.

1010
01:20:48,910 --> 01:20:51,078
Evelyn!

1011
01:20:51,080 --> 01:20:53,814
Max?

1012
01:20:53,816 --> 01:20:55,015
There's no need for this.

1013
01:20:55,017 --> 01:20:57,351
Stop where you are!

1014
01:20:58,420 --> 01:21:01,155
Put down the gun, Max.

1015
01:21:01,157 --> 01:21:02,356
[ Gunshot ]
Evelyn: No!

1016
01:21:02,358 --> 01:21:03,624
Evelyn, come here!

1017
01:21:03,626 --> 01:21:05,092
Why are you
so afraid of this?

1018
01:21:05,094 --> 01:21:06,727
[ Gunshot ]
Evelyn: No!

1019
